'''约旦河大裂谷'''（{{lang-ar|الغور}} ''Al-Ghor''或''Al-Ghawr''，{{lang-he-n|בִּקְעָת הַיַרְדֵּן}} ''Bik'at HaYarden''），位于[[以色列|以色列]]、[[约旦|约旦]]和[[巴勒斯坦|巴勒斯坦]]，是一个细长的谷地。地理意义上的区域包括从[[约旦河|约旦河]]的源头，到胡拉谷地，[[加利利海|加利利海]]，[[约旦河谷|约旦河谷]]，再到地球上的最低点[[死海|死海]]的整条[[约旦河|约旦河]]，然后穿过[[阿拉伯谷|阿拉伯谷]]，到[[亚喀巴湾|亚喀巴湾]]直到[[红海|红海]]。

==历史和物理特点==
[[File:Greatrift.jpg|thumb]]位于中心，死海和约旦河谷位于上方]]
约旦河大裂谷大约是在几百万年前的[[中新世|中新世]]，[[阿拉伯板块|阿拉伯板块]]向东北移动离开[[非洲|非洲]]时形成的（23.8－5.3百万年前）。一百万年后，地中海和大裂谷之间的地面抬升，因此海水停止了向裂谷裡涌入。

从各种在更深层的盆地保留的连续的[[沉积岩|沉积岩]]和[[岩浆岩|岩浆岩]]，可以看出自[[渐新世|渐新世]]以来的裂谷的地质和环境的演变。盆地周围露出的地层可以看出沉积和侵蚀的交替作用。<ref>[http://www.tau.ac.il/~archpubs/projects/horjordanriftvalley.html The Jordan Rift Valley] {{Wayback|url=http://www.tau.ac.il/~archpubs/projects/horjordanriftvalley.html |date=20150924125641 }}, [[特拉维夫大学|特拉维夫大学]]</ref>

大裂谷的最低点在[[死海|死海]]，比海平面低790米，地海沿岸也是地球上的最低点，比海平面低400米左右。在西部地形急剧抬升大约1000米，相似的，裂痕在东边也是显著的地形特点。<ref name=Eshel>{{cite web|title=Increasing Importance of the Jordan Rift Buffer|author=David Eshel|publisher=Defense Update|date=3 May 2006|url=http://www.defense-update.com/2006/05/increasing-importance-of-jordan-rift.html|access-date=2015-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705110711/http://www.defense-update.com/2006/05/increasing-importance-of-jordan-rift.html|archive-date=2008-07-05|dead-url=yes}}</ref>死海北部的裂谷由于约旦河水和两侧山上的泉水，被长期耕种。

==死海断层==
{{Main|死海断层}}

延伸到裂谷的[[阿拉伯板块|阿拉伯板块]]和[[非洲板块|非洲板块]]边界称为[[死海断层|死海断层]]，连接{{link-en|红海裂谷|Red Sea Rift}}和[[土耳其|土耳其]]的[[东安那托利亚断层|东安那托利亚断层]]。<ref>[http://www.gii.co.il/html/ground/GravityNew/DeadSeaStudy.html# The Geophysical Institute] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080623003339/http://www.gii.co.il/html/ground/GravityNew/DeadSeaStudy.html |date=2008-06-23 }}</ref>

死海断层通常被认为是[[转换断层|转换断层]]，阿拉伯板块已经移位约105公里。<ref name="Freund et al 1970">{{cite journal | url=http://rsta.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/267/1181/107.short | title=The Shear along the Dead Sea Rift (and Discussion) | author=Freund R., Garfunkel Z., Zak I., Goldberg M., Weissbrod T., Derin B., Bender F., Wellings F.E. & Girdler R.W. | journal=Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London. Series A, Mathematical and Physical Sciences | year=1970 | volume=267 | issue=1181 | doi=10.1098/rsta.1970.0027 | access-date=2015-11-14 | archive-date=2016-03-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304093045/http://rsta.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/267/1181/107.short | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Joffe & Garfunkel">{{cite journal | url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0040195187901715 | title=Plate kinematics of the circum Red Sea—a re-evaluation | author=Joffe S. & Garfunkel Z. | journal=Tectonophysics | year=1987 | volume=141 | issue=1-3 | pages=5–22 | doi=10.1016/0040-1951(87)90171-5 | access-date=2015-11-14 | archive-date=2019-07-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190707053735/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0040195187901715 | dead-url=no }}</ref>这种解释是根据对偏移标记的观测，如河流阶地、沟渠，在几百万年内大约每年偏移几毫米。<ref name="Begin & Steinitz">{{cite journal | url=http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Gideon_Steinitz/publication/249234276_Temporal_and_spatial_variations_of_microearthquake_activity_along_the_Dead_Sea_Fault_1984-2004/links/5494109f0cf2bd3178e6b716.pdf | title=Temporal and spatial variations of microearthquake activity along the Dead Sea Fault, 1984–2004 | author=Begin Z.B. & Steinitz G. | journal=Israel Journal of Earth Sciences | year=2005 | volume=54 | pages=1–14 | doi=10.1560/QTVW-HY1E-7XNU-JCLJ | access-date=2015-11-14 | archive-date=2017-08-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819233221/https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Gideon_Steinitz/publication/249234276_Temporal_and_spatial_variations_of_microearthquake_activity_along_the_Dead_Sea_Fault_1984-2004/links/5494109f0cf2bd3178e6b716.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>[[GPS|GPS]]的数据也证实了阿拉伯板块相对于非洲板块的每年的位移率。<ref name="Gomez_2007">{{cite journal | url=https://ecommons.library.cornell.edu/bitstream/1813/5436/1/Gomez2007_GJI_post-print.pdf | title=Global Positioning System measurements of strain accumulation and slip transfer through the restraining bend along the Dead Sea fault system in Lebanon | author=Gomez, F., Karam, G., Khawlie, M., McClusky S., Vernant P., Reilinger R., Jaafar R., Tabet C., Khair K., and Barazangi M | journal=Geophysical Journal International | year=2007 | volume=168 | issue=3 | pages=1021–1028 | doi=10.1111/j.1365-246X.2006.03328.x | bibcode=2007GeoJI.168.1021G | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713121041/https://ecommons.library.cornell.edu/bitstream/1813/5436/1/Gomez2007_GJI_post-print.pdf | archivedate=2015-07-13 }}</ref>也有人认为断裂带是初期海洋扩张中心的裂谷系，{{link-en|红海裂谷|Red Sea Rift}}的北部延伸。<ref name="Mart et al 2005">{{cite journal | url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0040195104003452 | title=Review of the tectonics of the Levant Rift system: the structural significance of oblique continental breakup | author=Mart Y., Ryan W.B.F. & Lunina O.V. | journal=Tectonophysics | year=2005 | volume=395 | issue=3-4 | pages=209–232 | doi=10.1016/j.tecto.2004.09.007 | access-date=2015-11-14 | archive-date=2018-11-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106140134/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0040195104003452 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

